<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-09-20T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-09-20T18:00:00-05:00" n="189" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d189">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">818.24/504: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Costa Rica</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Trueblood</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">San
                                            José</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-09-20T17:00:00-06:00">September 20, 1943—5
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 8:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>656. In view of Department’s 598, September 17 [<hi rend="italic">18</hi>], 10 p.m. [<hi rend="italic">11 a.m.</hi>] Minister of
                                Finance and Chief of Country Agency, have accepted in principle the
                                simplification of procedure Alternative III and the OEW announcement
                                may include Costa Rica among the countries participating.</p>
                            <p>Specific requests from the Country Agency concerning orders covered
                                by Import Recommendations and the preference to be granted goods
                                considered essential will follow.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Trueblood</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>